TY  - JOUR
T1  - Effects of Dyadic Quality and Duration on Performance Appraisal
AU  - Duarte, Neville T.
AU  - Goodson, Jane R.
AU  - Klich, Nancy R
Y1  - 1994/06/01
PY  - 1994
DA  - 1994/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256698
DO  - 10.5465/256698
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 499
EP  - 521
VL  - 37
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined the interactive influence of performance, the quality of a supervisor-subordinate relationship, and the duration of that relationship on performance ratings. The results suggest that, in both the short run and long run, the performance of employees in high- quality ?leader-member exchange? relationships is rated high, regardless of their objectively measured performance. The ratings of employees in low-quality exchange relationships are consistent with their objective performance in the short run but high in the long run, regardless of objective performance.
AB  - This study examined the interactive influence of performance, the quality of a supervisor-subordinate relationship, and the duration of that relationship on performance ratings. The results suggest that, in both the short run and long run, the performance of employees in high- quality ?leader-member exchange? relationships is rated high, regardless of their objectively measured performance. The ratings of employees in low-quality exchange relationships are consistent with their objective performance in the short run but high in the long run, regardless of objective performance.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256698
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256698
Y2  - 2026/04/24
